5:
Looks like you're hooked on her
music, huh, Sho?
9:
Says who? I'm not hooked. I'm just
stuck here chaperoning this guy.
12:
He was complaining about missing
Dia's last concert, after all. That's the
only reason I'm here!
17:
I did say I was interested in the
concert, but if I recall, you strongly
urged me to go see it. Multiple times.
22:
Huh? I mean... I wasn't wrong, was I?
It's worth seeing!
26:
You can't even be honest with
yourself, can you. No matter. I still
commend you for even getting
tickets.
30:
Oh, I just asked Regis for a favor on
that. I've been hanging out with him
a lot lately.
34:
I don't think the world is ready for a
duo like that...
39:
Actually, we agreed to meet up
here, but he's still nowhere—
46:
My apologies—we've an urgent
situation on our hands. Tonight's
performance has been cancelled... I
need your help.
57:
A pleasure to make your
acquaintance, Diva Media.
58:
I prepared this cage just for you. I
hope it is to your liking.
67:
How disappointing that you could
not tell. Do I look like a lapdog of the
Administrator?
73:
Looks like we're dealing with an
Updater.
77:
One of them, huh. They're on the
side of the revolution... Doesn't that
make them your allies?
82:
We share certain sentiments, yes,
but we are different. For one, they're
radicals. They're not the types I like
to associate with.
84:
Some of them take issue with the
fact that a certain little canary is still
singing those same "lullabies," even
after the Administrator's gone.
89:
So what, they kidnap her and try to
force her to shut up? That's messed
up!
94:
...We're almost there. I'm cutting off
the signal. Don't leave me without
backup in there!
104:
Regis is really out for blood. You can
tell this is personal for him.
107:
He might have called us here to
stop him from doing anything
drastic. Let's go.
113:
But I'm not the one you're really
after, am I?
116:
You don't really want to hear my
song. You don't believe in it or what
it stands for!
119:
No, your sights are set on Regis
instead.
122:
Our true savior, and the droid whose
visage shall be flown on our banners
is none other than Rec Register.
124:
He laid low the vile tyrant, freed
Central, and gave us the ability to
transcend our "human" limitations!
126:
Why would HE of all droids sit there
idly, a passive onlooker to such
great events? Why would he want to
spend his time with someone such
as you?
128:
So yes, you're correct. You are
nothing but bait to draw out Rec
Register.
132:
You'll get what you wish for. He'll
come here, all right. But it'll be to kill
you.
135: And I'll do my best to stop him.
164: I'm sorry. I'll be all right.
170:
I will. Don't worry. Just listen to my
song and rest.
178:
Regis, you and I traveled to a lot of
places, didn't we? To talk to all those
people who had lost their memories.
181:
But, I had a thought... What about
the people who lost their bodies?
People whose memories had
nowhere to return to?
186:
You mean those who lost their
Manabrain? In the world of people,
they'd become lingering spirits.
Ghosts, some call them.
190:
I first noticed them when I was in
need of help. I called for them with
my song, and they came to me.
They rescued me!
193:
But in reality, maybe they only came
to me to say goodbye.
220:
Oh, h-hello there. You're... Nova,
right? Stella's... coworker?
224:
Hahaha, I like that. "Coworker." We
did in fact share a workplace at one
point. You may also call me your
partner in crime, if you wish.
227:
I had planned to attend your
concert today. I'm happy that I got
to hear you sing despite the
cancellation.
231:
And yet you've got that melancholy
look on your face. The one Stella
sometimes makes.
235:
Perhaps it was your singing that
caused it?
237:
Your melodies draw out a pang of
pain within the breast. A feeling of
loneliness. One which we
abandoned ones know very well.
240:
But don't misunderstand me—your
singing was simply incredible. I look
forward to hearing it again.
244:
Well, in that case, would you like a
mini concert now?
247:
Since I didn't do a full concert today,
I've still got more energy in me! I'm
up for it, if you want to hear more!
251:
I very much would. Shall I invite Alk
and Shota?
256:
Why not! Invite everyone—whoever
you want!
260:
Everyone... Yes, it's much less lonely
with everyone around.
